channel.title: Help about aryan
channel.description:
jagex might be doign this to ban up
its easy as pie to get a list of running processes on a computer, when you run runescape it's a java engine that can take full control of your computer. it can get a list of programs running and send it back to jagex.
or does aryan changed the ID name in windows each use then it's harder if not impossible to find.

item.title: Help about aryan
item.dc:creator: @jme jme
item.description:
@jme wrote:

[quote=“DeadBird, post:4, topic:2731”][quote author=jme_009 link=topic=3002.msg28715#msg28715 date=1147482230]

wtf are you talking about???

He’s not talking like some noob, he has a very valid question.

Anyways, as of yet Im pretty sure that they dont check your proccesses, but I imagine in the future they will. Aryan si so detectable because it sends a negitive UID.
[/quote]
Leel.
Its not neg uid.
neg uid = 30 second ban
It has a *9999999 uid.[/quote]
Er… Well some ID was sending -1, when it was supposed to be 0. or at least thats what I heard.
